        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 12. Specimen (R 19 mm) of Luidia senegalensis (Lamarck, 1816) (UFBA 592): (A) abactinal and (B) actinal view of body; (C) paxillae of the central region of the arm; (D) madreporite hidden by paxillae; (E) paxillae in the arms; (F) oral region; (G) inferomarginal spines; (H) ambulacral furrow. Scale bars: A–B, 10 mm; C–E, G–H, 1 mm; F, 2 mm. (C–H) Photo credit: Alisson Santana." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4691110/files/figure.png" .

